userStories.notes:
Edit platform/shared/src/index.ts. The current types are:

- TabSyncAllParams (line ~239): { tabs: Record<string, { state: TabState; tabId: number | null; url: string | null }> }
- TabStateChangedParams (line ~231): { plugin: string; state: TabState; tabId: number | null; url: string | null }
- ToolDispatchParams (line ~222): { plugin: string; tool: string; input: Record<string, unknown> }

New PluginTabInfo type: { tabId: number; url: string; title: string; ready: boolean }

TabSyncAllParams becomes: { tabs: Record<string, { state: TabState; tabs: PluginTabInfo[] }> }
TabStateChangedParams becomes: { plugin: string; state: TabState; tabs: PluginTabInfo[] }
ToolDispatchParams becomes: { plugin: string; tool: string; input: Record<string, unknown>; tabId?: number }

This will break compilation in mcp-server and browser-extension — that is intentional. Downstream stories fix all consumers. The compile errors guide the work. Make sure every file that imports these types still compiles after updating the types AND the usage sites in shared/ itself (if any). Run npm run build from the repo root to verify.

IMPORTANT: Also update the TabMapping type in platform/mcp-server/src/state.ts from { state, tabId, url } to { state, tabs: PluginTabInfo[] }. The tabMapping Map<string, TabMapping> stays keyed by plugin name, but now each entry holds an array of tabs. Update all direct consumers of TabMapping in the server (extension-handlers.ts parseTabMapping, handleTabSyncAll, handleTabStateChanged; http-routes.ts health endpoint pluginDetails; extension-protocol.ts; mcp-setup.ts if referenced).

Do NOT change the extension code in this story — that is US-002's job. Focus only on platform/shared/ types and platform/mcp-server/ compile fixes for the new types. The server-side handlers (handleTabSyncAll, handleTabStateChanged) should be updated to parse the new wire format. The /health endpoint should expose all tabs per plugin, not just one.
